    "type": "message",
    "text": "<@U5STGTB3J> Thanks a lot for the input on this! Love that Herbert Simon paper. I could be wrong here but I think whole of category theory as a study of morphisms over topological entities has the same layered graph idea as the it's central unifying metaphor. I am thinking more about things like perceptrons of Minsky (which is again a neural network ~ graph), or Ulf Grenander like pattern generators, may be even composing cellular automata together to build and reason about complex systems.",
