  {
    "client_msg_id": "ec0d86c7-6ec0-44ca-a2db-45f5f2c1ed09",
    "type": "message",
    "text": "<@UJPHQ8Z3N> No, i and i + 1, I consider as discrete computations which may or may not have the same time (concurrent computations). I am aware about TimeCapsule and there's this whole paper on state of the art graph visualization techniques here: <https://pdfs.semanticscholar.org/a4db/7fdb7224456e98bd41b6803b5fb29296ec01.pdf> I want to explore more fundamental building blocks other than dot and arrow model of graph theory to build bigger systems.",
